10 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 14-135, which relates to career-readiness
11 assessments; directing the State Department of
Education, rather than the Oklahoma Department of
12 Commerce, in certain cooperation to approve certain
assessments and credentials; removing language making
13 such approval subject to funding; directing the
assessments to be made available to students in
14 certain grades beginning in certain school year;
directing the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
15 Education in certain consultation to promulgate
certain rules; providing an effective date; and
16 declaring an emergency.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 14-135, is
21 amended to read as follows:
22 Section 14-135. Subject to the availability of funds, beginning
23 with the 2019-2020 school year, the Oklahoma Department of Commerce,
24 in cooperation with the
SB1632 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. The State Department of Education and, in cooperation with
2 the Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability, shall
3 review and approve career-readiness assessments and assessment-based
4 credentials that measure and document foundational workplace skills.
5 Beginning with the 2019-2020 2026-2027 school year, the assessments
6 shall be made available to all public school districts to be
7 administered to students at the discretion of each school district’s
8 administration to students in grades ten through twelve at least
9 once prior to their graduation from high school. The assessment-
10 based credential shall be available to any student who achieves the
11 prescribed level on the required assessments assessment. If the
12 public school district chooses to administer the assessments, the
13 assessments shall be administered at least once to each student who
14 chooses to take the assessment at no cost to the student. The
15 assessments shall:
16 1. Be a standardized, criterion-referenced measure of broadly
17 relevant foundational workplace skills;
18 2. Assess and document student readiness for a wide range of
19 jobs;
20 3. Measure skills in the following areas, including, but not
21 limited to:
22 a. applied mathematics,
23 b. workplace documents,
24 c. graphic literacy, or
SB1632 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 d. critical thinking and leadership collaboration;
2 4. Align with research-based skill requirement profiles for
3 specific industries and occupations;
4 5. Lead to nationally recognized work-readiness certificates or
5 credentials for students who meet the minimum proficiency
6 requirements on the component assessments; and
7 6. Be available in paper- and computer-based formats.
8 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, in
9 consultation with the American Council on Education National Guide,
10 may promulgate rules to allow institutions of higher education
11 within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education to grant
12 college credit based on assessment-based credentials and scores
13 earned on career-readiness assessments.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
15 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
19
